Lauri Koskela (May 16, 1907, Lapua  August 3, 1944) was a Finnish wrestler and Olympic champion in Greco-Roman wrestling. Koskela competed at the 1936 Summer Olympics in Berlin where he received a gold medal in Greco-Roman wrestling, the lightweight class.[1] He received a bronze medal at the 1932 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles. 
